<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="362" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/368</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MCK1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moser</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-23T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 23,
                                            1918, 5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>For <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>:</p>
                            <p>Ambassador, Vologda, requests that <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> be sent immediately with two to five
                                engineers to Vologda to confer about transportation. Ambassador
                                promises special car and safe-conduct. Department approves. Advise
                                Ambassador when <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> can
                                leave, notifying the Department at same time. If absence of
                                    <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Emerson</persName> would interfere
                                with your work on Chinese Eastern send next best man available.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>